11:
N-no... It's nothing, 
I'm just... Doesn't this outfit 
look a little strange on me?
16: Not at all! It suits you perfectly.
21:
Th-thank you, Captain Alk. But... 
I can't help but feel embarrassed!
26:
Weren't you the one who said she
wanted to wear something festive?
It looks good on you, so have a little
confidence.
30:
If it really bothers you, it isn't too late
to turn down the role of Santa Claus.
I'm sure Lilie doesn't want to make
you uncomfortable.
35:
N-no! 
I... I want to do this.
44:
It's okay, Fluffy. 
You look adorable.
52:
Ah... 
I'm not used to praise like this...
58:
Halt! 
State your name and business
h—
64:
Looks like you're as sharp as ever,
Corporal Fluffy... As sharp as the
pain in my back!
67:
I gotta admit, I had my doubts 
when I first saw that outfit... 
But I'm impressed.
71:
Yes, sir! I've been training day and
night—
74:
Impressed by how CUTE you are!
Wow!
82:
Hello again, everyone. I'm glad to
see you all doing well.
85:
I'm sorry for my aggressive
approach earlier. I guess I can't help
myself.
88:
Not at all... That's how the captain
was, too.
91:
Now, regarding the invitation for me
to join your unit, I apologize for
keeping you waiting for so long.
95:
...I'm sorry. I've found a new life, 
and I won't be returning 
to the military.
98:
...I expected as much. I know you've
got your reasons.
101:
Thank you, Sergeant. I've been quite
busy, exploring ruins and accepting
requests from the Guild...
104:
I've grown very fond of my new life
together with the other adventurers.
108:
That said... I'm still only useful in
combat...
111:
Hey, Corporal. Do you always wear
that outfit when adventuring?
115:
N-no, I don't! I just accepted a
request to play the role of Santa,
and—
118:
If our little Fluffy is old enough to be
Santa... then the rest of us must
REALLY be over the hill.
121:
I don't really know if I should be the
one playing Santa, though... I'm not
even familiar with the customs of
the season.
124:
Maybe just handing out presents in
accordance with the request won't
be good enough...
128:
What kind of Santa would you like to
be, Fluffy?
135:
I... want to help out orphans like
myself, as well as any children who
are suffering alone... I want them to
know they belong just as much as
everybody else.
138:
Orphans like you, huh... Come to
think of it, we never could give you
the childhood you deserved.
140:
...Having the captain cook meals for
you was probably the closest thing
to a normal childhood experience
you got to have.
143:
Ah... That's right! Cooking! 
I wonder if I could be a Santa 
who gives out food?
146:
I think the children would love to eat
something special made just for
them.
154:
Something festive and edible to give
to kids, huh? How about baking a
cake?
160:
Cake! I've got next to no experience
with baking, but I'd love to give it a
try!
163:
...Perfect. We happen to have a
former pastry chef with us. He can
show you the ropes.
165:
Private Marco, reporting for duty!
With your leave, I'll teach you all
about baking a cake!
174:
Fluffy! You're nothing but a helpless
newborn, too small and useless to
do anything alone!
176:
Tell me what somebody as pathetic
as you needs to do to make a cake!
189:
If the recipe says to bake something
at low heat for five minutes, then
you bake at low heat for five
minutes.
191:
Don't tell yourself "I'll bake at high
heat for one minute and save time."
Don't ignore the recipe unless you're
looking for a one-way ticket to Hell!
198:
...Question time. How many minutes
would you wait if you DID use high
heat?
204:
What did I just say!? Follow the
RECIPE! Drop and give me twenty!
212:
Don't you think you're the one who
should be teaching her?
216:
Now, now. Let's not step on
anybody's toes.
221: Fluffy looks like she's having fun.
224:
It's thanks to you. Not only is she
smiling more, she can act and think
for herself now, too.
226:
...That was something we could
never do. And for that, you have our
thanks.
228: Not at all. Fluffy did it all by herself—
232:
HOWEVER! We can thank you all day
for how you helped her, but getting
INVOLVED with her is another matter
entirely!
238:
If you and Corporal Fluffy start going
out one day, the pain you'll be
inflicting on us will—
249:
Wh-what are you saying?! Captain
Alk isn't anything like that!
252:
Corporal Fluffy! Are you learning
how to bake, or are you trying to get
married?
256:
Huh?! I'm trying to become Santa
Claus! Sir!
259:
Then calm down and FOCUS! 
But first, drop and give me fifty!
267:
I... I'll be the best Santa Claus there
ever was!
